text: Chesterfield County is a county in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2020 census, it has 43,273 people living there. Its county seat is Chesterfield. and largest city in the county is Cheraw. It is on the northern border with North Carolina. Chesterfield County is located in the Pee Dee region of South Carolina. == References == Category:1785 establishments in South Carolina Category:South Carolina counties
